{"type":"message","id":"47fb5df5","parentId":"0c04e193","timestamp":"2026-03-25T17:15:57.815Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_t1GhTJ3daO3x6Jmcuxa1zUpZ","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenClaw acpx runtime plugin install\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 2055,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"49b4349ba91335de\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nacpx/README.md at main · openclaw/acpx - GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"49b4349ba91335de\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/acpx/blob/main/README.md\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1f8b65cfd1a20bd3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIt will install acpx, read the skill reference, and know how to use ACP for all future coding agent tasks. I want you to use acpx to run coding agents over the\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1f8b65cfd1a20bd3\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999379\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e57edf0cd85d5531\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nACP Agents - OpenClaw Docs\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e57edf0cd85d5531\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/acp-agents\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7dca0a95000ef266\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# ​ ACP agents. | Runtime | ACP backend plugin (for example acpx) | OpenClaw native sub-agent runtime |. | Spawn tool | `sessions_spawn` with `runtime:\\\"acp\\\"` | `sessions_spawn` (default runtime) |. ## ​ Start ACP sessions (interfaces). `Use the sessions_spawn tool now with runtime: \\\"acp\\\", agentId: \\\"codex\\\", and mode: \\\"run\\\". `Sandboxed sessions cannot spawn ACP sessions because runtime=\\\"acp\\\" runs on the host. `sessions_spawn sandbox=\\\"require\\\" is unsupported for runtime=\\\"acp\\\" because ACP sessions run outside the sandbox. ### ​ From `/acp` command. /acp spawn codex --thread here`. ## ​ ACP controls. | `/acp spawn` | Create ACP session; optional thread bind. | `/acp set-mode` | Set runtime mode for target session. | Use `runtime=\\\"subagent\\\"` from sandboxed sessions, or run ACP spawn from a non-sandboxed session. | `sessions_spawn sandbox=\\\"require\\\" is unsupported for runtime=\\\"acp\\\" ...` | `sandbox=\\\"require\\\"` requested for ACP runtime. | Use `runtime=\\\"subagent\\\"` for required sandboxing, or use ACP with `sandbox=\\\"inherit\\\"` from a non-sandboxed session. `sessions_spawn sandbox=\\\"require\\\" is unsupported for runtime=\\\"acp\\\" ...`.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7dca0a95000ef266\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999145\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b65f5e91c4d7dac8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPlugins - OpenClaw Docs\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b65f5e91c4d7dac8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/plugin\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f51b63e159e4575c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n##### Plugins. # Plugins. # ​ Plugins. openclaw plugins install @openclaw/voice-call. openclaw plugins install ./my-plugin. openclaw plugins install ./my-plugin.tgz`. `/plugin install clawhub:@openclaw/voice-call. ## ​ Plugin types. | **Native** | `openclaw.plugin.json` + runtime module; executes in-process | Official plugins, community npm packages |. ## ​ Official plugins. ### ​ Core (shipped with OpenClaw). | `entries.\\\\<id\\\\>` | Per-plugin toggles + config |. `plugins.entries.\\\\<id\\\\>.enabled: false`. ## ​ Plugin slots (exclusive categories). contextEngine: \\\"legacy\\\", // or a plugin id. `openclaw plugins list # compact inventory. openclaw plugins inspect <id> # deep detail. openclaw plugins inspect <id> --json # machine-readable. openclaw plugins status # operational summary. openclaw plugins install <package> # install (ClawHub first, then npm). openclaw plugins install clawhub:<pkg> # install from ClawHub only. openclaw plugins install <path> # install from local path. openclaw plugins install -l <path> # link (no copy) for dev. openclaw plugins update <id> # update one plugin. openclaw plugins update --all # update all. ## ​ Plugin API overview.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f51b63e159e4575c\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9998623\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"15ac2bc9bc2bda9e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nACPX runtime fails on nix-openclaw immutable store (plugin tries to ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"15ac2bc9bc2bda9e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/nix-openclaw/issues/73\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc0e569b06c3ac81\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Search code, repositories, users, issues, pull requests... # ACPX runtime fails on nix-openclaw immutable store (plugin tries to write node\\\\_modules under /nix/store) #73. ACPX runtime fails on nix-openclaw immutable store (plugin tries to write node\\\\_modules under /nix/store)#73. When ACPX runtime is enabled in nix-openclaw, the plugin loads but ACP sessions fail with:. Gateway logs show ACPX trying to create/install plugin-local dependencies inside `/nix/store`, which is read-only. * OpenClaw gateway package from nix store. mkdir '/nix/store/.../extensions/acpx/node_modules/acpx'`. On Nix (immutable package paths), ACPX should start without attempting writes to plugin directory under `/nix/store`. 1. Enable ACPX runtime plugin in nix-openclaw config. * Resolve `acpx` binary from packaged dependency path (or configurable command) instead of plugin-local install. How it could work upstream (design): package acpx with gateway and have the ACPX plugin use that binary directly first, with plugin-local install only as a non-Nix fallback. No fields configured for issues without a type. ## Issue actions.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc0e569b06c3ac81\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99985576\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef11ef93b65b7c70\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nacp-router | Skills Marketplace - LobeHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef11ef93b65b7c70\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://lobehub.com/de/skills/openclaw-openclaw-acp-router\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1dbb88d1ef49966c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nacp-router is a centralized routing skill that translates plain-language requests for Pi, Claude Code, Codex, OpenCode, Gemini CLI, or ACP harness tasks into the appropriate execution path: OpenClaw ACP runtime sessions or direct acpx-driven sessions (the “telephone game” flow). Key features include destination mapping, request normalization, extensible LLM-to-runtime rules, routing fallbacks, and consistent session creation that improves reliability and interoperability across agent ecosystems. When user intent is \\\"run this in Pi/Claude Code/Codex/OpenCode/Gemini/Kimi (ACP harness)\\\", do not use subagent runtime or PTY scraping. P9 Tech Lead mode — write Task Prompts, manage P8 agent teams, never write code yourself. When the user asks to start a coding harness in a thread (for example \\\"start a codex/claude/pi/kimi thread\\\"), treat that as an ACP runtime request and try to satisfy it end-to-end. Use this path to drive harness sessions without `/acp` or subagent runtime. `${ACPX_CMD} codex sessions show oc-codex-<conversationId> \\\\. || ${ACPX_CMD} codex sessions new --name oc-codex-<conversationId>. `${ACPX_CMD} <agent> sessions new --name <sessionName>`.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1dbb88d1ef49966c\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.999488