{"type":"message","id":"c1c858ba","parentId":"c8ee5a10","timestamp":"2026-03-25T18:10:43.992Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring browser connections**\n\nSince we're using a chat tool, I think I should try executing a PowerShell command to detect any existing Brave processes. If I find one, ideally, I could use Playwright to connect to that running browser. However, I realize it's tricky since Brave isn't directly launched by Playwright. While Brave does support remote debugging, it relies on a specific port, which might not be enabled in any existing session. Still, I'll check if Brave is running to decide my next steps.**Considering automation limitations**\n\nI realize that without acpx, automation isn't an option. However, I can fetch a YouTube video link as a workaround. The user is curious about checking for an existing Brave session to play the video. I’ll let them know I tried checking for a Brave session, but since acpx isn’t configured, I can't automate it. Instead, I can suggest manual steps to focus the existing Brave window and navigate to the video. I'll use PowerShell to check for any running Brave processes.**Preparing to check Brave processes**\n\nI’m planning to make a tool call using PowerShell to check for any running Brave processes by executing the command: `Get-Process Brave -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Id,ProcessName,StartTime`. This will return some data in JSON, which I will need to parse effectively.\n\nIf I find any Brave processes, my response will indicate that with their IDs. If none are found, I’ll notify the user accordingly. I’ll also suggest that if a Brave session is active with DevTools enabled, they might need to manually click to play the video or open the URL directly.**Exploring Playwright options**\n\nI’m considering using Playwright to try attaching to an existing Brave browser instance through its wsEndpoint, but I don’t have that information. My next step is to check for any running Brave processes; I’ll let the user know if I find one or not. \n\nIf they want to use an existing Brave window, they’ll need to enable remote debugging or provide the endpoint. Otherwise, we could open a new tab in Brave later if acpx is configured. I can also guide them to manually open Brave and go to the video link or use a direct YouTube link.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_G8fOus5LSEEsHofMVgcDrIsM","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -NoProfile -Command \"Get-Process Brave -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Id,ProcessName,StartTime\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":20592,"output":1871,"cacheRead":3712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26175,"cost":{"input":-20592,"output":-1871,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-22463}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774462225221,"responseId":"gen-1774462225-f5L2ux7snHsYXetRAfrV"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f103fcb","parentId":"c1c858ba","timestamp":"2026-03-25T18:10:44.640Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_G8fOus5LSEEsHofMVgcDrIsM","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Id ProcessName StartTime            \r\n   -- ----------- ---------            \r\n 2004 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:22 PM \r\n 3916 brave       3/25/2026 10:59:40 PM\r\n 3924 brave       3/26/2026 1:02:17 AM \r\n 4528 brave       3/25/2026 8:03:55 PM \r\n 4660 brave       3/25/2026 11:26:19 PM\r\n 4716 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:22 PM \r\n 7496 brave       3/26/2026 1:09:35 AM \r\n 7840 brave       3/26/2026 1:09:52 AM \r\n 9416 brave       3/25/2026 8:04:02 PM \r\n 9884 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:21 PM \r\n10432 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:22 PM \r\n12084 brave       3/25/2026 7:58:04 PM \r\n13048 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:21 PM \r\n13172 brave       3/25/2026 10:59:43 PM\r\n14672 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:22 PM \r\n16588 brave       3/25/2026 11:08:15 PM\r\n16656 brave       3/25/2026 10:38:43 PM\r\n16844 brave       3/25/2026 10:39:04 PM\r\n17216 brave       3/25/2026 10:39:06 PM"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":551,"aggregated":"Id ProcessName StartTime            \r\n   -- ----------- ---------            \r\n 2004 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:22 PM \r\n 3916 brave       3/25/2026 10:59:40 PM\r\n 3924 brave       3/26/2026 1:02:17 AM \r\n 4528 brave       3/25/2026 8:03:55 PM \r\n 4660 brave       3/25/2026 11:26:19 PM\r\n 4716 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:22 PM \r\n 7496 brave       3/26/2026 1:09:35 AM \r\n 7840 brave       3/26/2026 1:09:52 AM \r\n 9416 brave       3/25/2026 8:04:02 PM \r\n 9884 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:21 PM \r\n10432 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:22 PM \r\n12084 brave       3/25/2026 7:58:04 PM \r\n13048 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:21 PM \r\n13172 brave       3/25/2026 10:59:43 PM\r\n14672 brave       3/25/2026 7:57:22 PM \r\n16588 brave       3/25/2026 11:08:15 PM\r\n16656 brave       3/25/2026 10